"title": "8332: reputation",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8332",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The estimation of a person in the sight of God or other people. Scripture stresses the importance of believers having a good reputation with those outside the faith.</p>\n<h2>God's defence of his own reputation</h2>\n<h3>God's actions in history to uphold his reputation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:13-Exod9:16\">EXO 9:13–9:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:9-Ezek20:10\">EZK 20:9–20:10</a></p>\n<h3>God's rebukes his people for failing to uphold his reputation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:2\">MAL 2:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:6-Mal1:11\">MAL 1:6–1:11</a></p>\n<h3>God's promises to uphold his reputation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:22-Ezek36:23\">EZK 36:22–36:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:8\">ISA 42:8</a></p>\n<h2>The reputation of believers</h2>\n<h3>Believers must seek a good reputation with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:16\">ACT 24:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:9-2Cor5:10\">2CO 5:9–5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:1\">1TH 4:1</a></p>\n<h3>Believers must have a good reputation with outsiders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:13-Acts5:16\">ACT 5:13–5:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:46-Acts2:47\">ACT 2:46–2:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:16\">ACT 24:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:7\">1TI 3:7</a></p>\n<h3>Believers must not boast to improve their own reputation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:17-2Cor10:18\">2CO 10:17–10:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:5-1Cor3:7\">1CO 3:5–3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:4-Phil3:9\">PHP 3:4–3:9</a></p>\n<h3>Believers must not seek a good reputation through outward show</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:16-Matt6:18\">MAT 6:16–6:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:1-Matt6:8\">MAT 6:1–6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:2-Matt23:12\">MAT 23:2–23:12</a></p>\n<h3>Believers may find that serving God leads to a bad reputation with unbelievers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:5-Acts17:8\">ACT 17:5–17:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:1-1Kgs19:5\">1KI 19:1–19:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:1-Luke23:2\">LUK 23:1–23:2</a></p>\n<h2>Good reputations</h2>\n<h3>Examples of God-fearers with a good reputation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:3-Luke7:5\">LUK 7:3–7:5</a> <em>the centurion</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:1-Acts10:4\">ACT 10:1–10:4</a> <em>Cornelius</em></p>\n<h3>Examples of believers with a good reputation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:3-Dan6:5\">DAN 6:3–6:5</a> <em>Daniel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:36-Acts9:39\">ACT 9:36–9:39</a> <em>Dorcas</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:1-Acts16:2\">ACT 16:1–16:2</a> <em>Timothy</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:12-Acts22:13\">ACT 22:12–22:13</a> <em>Ananias</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:8\">ROM 1:8</a> <em>the church at Rome</em></p>\n<h3>The blessing of a good reputation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:1\">PRO 22:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:1\">ECC 7:1</a></p>\n<h2>Bad repuations</h2>\n<h3>The reputation of sinners is known to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:20-Gen18:21\">GEN 18:20–18:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:1-Rev3:2\">REV 3:1–3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:4-Rev18:5\">REV 18:4–18:5</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of reputed sinners</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:29-1Kgs16:33\">1KI 16:29–16:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:25-1Kgs21:26\">1KI 21:25–21:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:16-2Kgs21:17\">2KI 21:16–21:17</a></p>\n<h2>Outward reputation cannot compare with a righteous heart</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:7\">1SA 16:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:14-1Chr29:19\">1CH 29:14–29:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:1-Rev3:3\">REV 3:1–3:3</a></p>",
